2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the quality of service (QoS) requirements, which is a key concept in information theory. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may touch upon security issues in the HSR communication system, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a novel service model and scheduling algorithm, which can be considered as a control problem. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses a stochastic network optimization approach, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence.
